# 🎮 PRODUCT VISION

Habit Pet is a virtual companion game where users grow a dragon through real-life habit completion.

The pet is the emotional core.

The habit system is supportive gameplay.

The experience must feel:

- Warm
- Rewarding
- Cute
- Addictive (positive reinforcement)
- Never punishing

---

# 🧠 CORE GAME LOOP

Habit completion → XP → Level → Pet evolution → Rewards → Motivation loop

---

# 🎁 REWARD SYSTEM (CRITICAL ARCHITECTURE)

All rewards flow through:

RewardEventBus → RewardQueue → RewardManager → UI Overlay

NO direct UI triggering allowed.

---

# 🎯 REWARD PRIORITY ORDER

1. LevelUpReward (HIGHEST PRIORITY)
2. DragonEvolutionReward (NEW SYSTEM)
3. StreakReward
4. ChestReward
5. AchievementReward
6. CoinReward (NO POPUP UI)

---

# 🧱 REWARD UI RULES

- LevelUpReward → Full-screen immersive UI
- DragonEvolutionReward → Full-screen transition UI
- ChestReward → Full-screen chest animation UI
- AchievementReward → lightweight overlay
- CoinReward → silent (no UI)

All major rewards MUST be sequential.

User must dismiss each screen manually before next appears.

---

# 🐉 DRAGON EVOLUTION SYSTEM (NEW)

When pet evolves:

- Emit `DragonEvolutionReward`
- Show full-screen transition
- Initially use static image swap (old → new stage)
- Later replace with animation/video without architecture change

---

# 🎬 FULL-SCREEN OVERLAY RULE

Reward screens:

- Block navigation
- Use immersive mode
- Must cover entire screen
- Must support tap-to-continue flow
- Must never overlap

---

# 🐉 PET SYSTEM

Single dragon species:

Stages:
- Egg
- Hatchling
- Young Dragon
- Adult Dragon
- Ancient Dragon

Evolution is based on lifetime XP.

---

# 📦 XP + LEVEL SYSTEM

- XP increases level
- Level-up triggers LevelUpReward
- Level-up ALWAYS triggers ChestReward AFTER completion

---

# 🎁 CHEST SYSTEM

Triggered by:
- 7-day streak
- milestone streaks
- level-up bonus

Uses:
- chest_closed.png → chest_open.png transition

Future upgrade:
- replace with animation/video system

---

# 🧠 EVENT SYSTEM RULE

All game events must go through:

ViewModel → Domain logic → RewardEventBus → RewardQueue

No direct UI calls.

---

# 🎨 UI DESIGN RULES

- Game-like feel
- Soft gradients
- Rounded UI
- Full-screen reward moments
- No spreadsheet-style layouts

---

# ⚡ PERFORMANCE RULE

Prefer:

- simple state flows
- minimal coroutine scopes
- no unnecessary abstraction
- reuse existing systems

---

# 🧪 DEBUGGING RULE

